4629 bool Type::canHaveNullability(bool ResultIfUnknown) const {
4630  QualType type = getCanonicalTypeInternal();
4631 
4632  switch (type->getTypeClass()) {
4633  // We'll only see canonical types here.
4634 #define NON_CANONICAL_TYPE(Class, Parent) \
4635  case Type::Class: \
4636  llvm_unreachable("non-canonical type");
4637 #define TYPE(Class, Parent)
4638 #include "clang/AST/TypeNodes.inc"
4639 
4640  // Pointer types.
4641  case Type::Pointer:
4642  case Type::BlockPointer:
4643  case Type::MemberPointer:
4644  case Type::ObjCObjectPointer:
4645  return true;
4646 
4647  // Dependent types that could instantiate to pointer types.
4648  case Type::UnresolvedUsing:
4649  case Type::TypeOfExpr:
4650  case Type::TypeOf:
4651  case Type::Decltype:
4652  case Type::PackIndexing:
4653  case Type::UnaryTransform:
4654  case Type::TemplateTypeParm:
4655  case Type::SubstTemplateTypeParmPack:
4656  case Type::DependentName:
4657  case Type::DependentTemplateSpecialization:
4658  case Type::Auto:
4659  return ResultIfUnknown;
4660 
4661  // Dependent template specializations could instantiate to pointer types.
4662  case Type::TemplateSpecialization:
4663  // If it's a known class template, we can already check if it's nullable.
4664  if (TemplateDecl *templateDecl =
4665  cast<TemplateSpecializationType>(type.getTypePtr())
4666  ->getTemplateName()
4667  .getAsTemplateDecl())
4668  if (auto *CTD = dyn_cast<ClassTemplateDecl>(templateDecl))
4669  return CTD->getTemplatedDecl()->hasAttr<TypeNullableAttr>();

4671 
4672  case Type::Builtin:
4673  switch (cast<BuiltinType>(type.getTypePtr())->getKind()) {
4674  // Signed, unsigned, and floating-point types cannot have nullability.
4675 #define SIGNED_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
4676 #define UNSIGNED_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
4677 #define FLOATING_TYPE(Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
4678 #define BUILTIN_TYPE(Id, SingletonId)
4679 #include "clang/AST/BuiltinTypes.def"
4680  return false;
4681 
4682  // Dependent types that could instantiate to a pointer type.
4683  case BuiltinType::Dependent:
4684  case BuiltinType::Overload:
4685  case BuiltinType::BoundMember:
4686  case BuiltinType::PseudoObject:
4687  case BuiltinType::UnknownAny:
4688  case BuiltinType::ARCUnbridgedCast:
4689  return ResultIfUnknown;
4690 
4691  case BuiltinType::Void:
4692  case BuiltinType::ObjCId:
4693  case BuiltinType::ObjCClass:
4694  case BuiltinType::ObjCSel:
4695 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
4696  case BuiltinType::Id:
4697 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
4698 #define IMAGE_TYPE(ImgType, Id, SingletonId, Access, Suffix) \
4699  case BuiltinType::Sampled##Id:
4700 #define IMAGE_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
4701 #define IMAGE_READ_WRITE_TYPE(Type, Id, Ext)
4702 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLImageTypes.def"
4703 #define EXT_OPAQUE_TYPE(ExtType, Id, Ext) \
4704  case BuiltinType::Id:
4705 #include "clang/Basic/OpenCLExtensionTypes.def"
4706  case BuiltinType::OCLSampler:
4707  case BuiltinType::OCLEvent:
4708  case BuiltinType::OCLClkEvent:
4709  case BuiltinType::OCLQueue:
4710  case BuiltinType::OCLReserveID:
4711 #define SVE_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) \
4712  case BuiltinType::Id:
4713 #include "clang/Basic/AArch64SVEACLETypes.def"
4714 #define PPC_VECTOR_TYPE(Name, Id, Size) \
4715  case BuiltinType::Id:
4716 #include "clang/Basic/PPCTypes.def"
4717 #define RVV_TYPE(Name, Id, SingletonId) case BuiltinType::Id:
4718 #include "clang/Basic/RISCVVTypes.def"

4722  case BuiltinType::NullPtr:
4723  case BuiltinType::IncompleteMatrixIdx:
4724  case BuiltinType::OMPArraySection:
4725  case BuiltinType::OMPArrayShaping:

4730 
4731  case Type::Record: {

4803 bool Type::isBlockCompatibleObjCPointerType(ASTContext &ctx) const {
4804  const auto *objcPtr = getAs<ObjCObjectPointerType>();
4805  if (!objcPtr)
4806  return false;
4807 
4808  if (objcPtr->isObjCIdType()) {
4809  // id is always okay.
4810  return true;
4811  }
4812 
4813  // Blocks are NSObjects.
4814  if (ObjCInterfaceDecl *iface = objcPtr->getInterfaceDecl()) {
4815  if (iface->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSObjectName())
4816  return false;
4817 
4818  // Continue to check qualifiers, below.
4819  } else if (objcPtr->isObjCQualifiedIdType()) {
4820  // Continue to check qualifiers, below.
4821  } else {
4822  return false;
4823  }
4824 
4825  // Check protocol qualifiers.
4826  for (ObjCProtocolDecl *proto : objcPtr->quals()) {
4827  // Blocks conform to NSObject and NSCopying.
4828  if (proto->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSObjectName() &&
4829  proto->getIdentifier() != ctx.getNSCopyingName())
4830  return false;
4831  }
4832 
4833  return true;
4834 }

4930 bool Type::hasSizedVLAType() const {

4932

4935  if (const auto *ref = getAs<ReferenceType>())

4937  if (const ArrayType *arr = getAsArrayTypeUnsafe()) {

4944

4948 QualType::DestructionKind QualType::isDestructedTypeImpl(QualType type) {
4949  switch (type.getObjCLifetime()) {
4950  case Qualifiers::OCL_None:
4951  case Qualifiers::OCL_ExplicitNone:
4952  case Qualifiers::OCL_Autoreleasing:
4953  break;
4954 
4955  case Qualifiers::OCL_Strong:
4956  return DK_objc_strong_lifetime;
4957  case Qualifiers::OCL_Weak:
4958  return DK_objc_weak_lifetime;
4959  }
4960 
4961  if (const auto *RT =
4962  type->getBaseElementTypeUnsafe()->getAs<RecordType>()) {
4963  const RecordDecl *RD = RT->getDecl();
4964  if (const auto *CXXRD = dyn_cast<CXXRecordDecl>(RD)) {
4965  /// Check if this is a C++ object with a non-trivial destructor.
4966  if (CXXRD->hasDefinition() && !CXXRD->hasTrivialDestructor())
4967  return DK_cxx_destructor;
4968  } else {
4969  /// Check if this is a C struct that is non-trivial to destroy or an array
4970  /// that contains such a struct.
4971  if (RD->isNonTrivialToPrimitiveDestroy())
4972  return DK_nontrivial_c_struct;
4973  }
4974  }
4975 
4976  return DK_none;
4977 }
